caption: We ordered four Korean corn dogs and it took them an hour to prepare 3 and ended up refunding us for the last corn dog as they had 'no idea how long the other one would take to prepare'. Seriously! If they could have just warned us when they were taking our order that it would take sometime to prepare, I wouldn't be as mad and frustrated as I was. To top that, the ppl working there didn't seem to be really bothered by the fact the customers were unhappy. It was like they were doing us a favor. The three corn dogs that we managed to eat were sub-par at best. This place doesn't deserve any stars. Totally ruined that day of our trip!

Mozzarella spicy chicken was pretty good with a big portion. The mozzarella dog was crispy but not exactly the best tasting. It was okay.  I ordered for delivery at 7:18 through their website when I clicked “order online” and surprisingly the delivery company never received my order after waiting an hour. I called the restaurant at 8:46 and the individual at the restaurant who spoke with me over the phone was very helpful and thankfully after 10 minutes later my food had arrived.
looking forward to a return trip. bring your hunger - portions are large. kinda of like a restaurant in los angeles i loved to visit.
The staff was very friendly and kind. The place has a cool atmosphere. Food is similar to a place in San Francisco I liked.
I will be back with my coworkers. This place has a nice feel to it.
It's so delicious. The prices are well within reason for the quality.
A preferred evening place. The place has a cool atmosphere.
Service treated us so nice. The place has a nice atmosphere.

To start off with some praise, the wings were fantastic. Great flavor, very large, and crispy. However, the Bulgogi Dosirak,, which is a signature dish was absolutely horrible. It was bone dry, it was mostly shredded up veggies with a few scattered pieces of fatty beef. Also, the flavor was almost like a Mexican fajita, very weak flavor. It is a shame because the wings were so good---but at $18 for the awful bulgogi, I don't think I can return.
Had the Daekbak Combo that feeds four people (we were three) and were thoroughly satisfied. The staff were very courteous and positively added to our experience. We will certainly be back!
came in on a weds. service is consistently good.

When we discovered this place a year ago, we were ecstatic. It was inexpensive and taste great. We drove 1.5 hrs from the burbs to just come here. This week after months long of pandemic scare we again drove to just come here and we were hugely disappointed. Prices have sky rocketed! All the side dishes (raddish kimchi, kimchi and etc) are no longer free and comes with the meal. Its almost $5 if you want to order one. WHAT? Not sure if they have new chef, but the food is no longer taste as good as it used to be. Time to find a new place. Ahh well.
This place is nice and broad, the food was yummy and the prices were very fair. quickly, effective service and very amiable waiters. Highly recommended.

Love their spicy tofu seafood soup. Was saddened before when we weren't able to order it for takeout. We went in for chatime last night and to my surprise, they have it for takeout now! Pretty much their whole Daebak menu aside from the grill meat portion in downstairs. Can't wait for the summertime so I can try out their bingsu!

Food: below average. I ordered the stone bowl bibimbap and the grilled mackerel, and my friend ordered the spicy squid.  The bibimbap was basic but had too much rice and the bulgogi was pale and mediocre. The mackerel was served without lemons and was close to flavorless. It also came with banchan which were all disgusting and tasted like they had been dug out of a cellar. There were 4 items on the banchan (which they sell separately for $5): stale pickled radish which compressed as you bit into it, stale fish tofu which tasted like dessicated sticks of gum, boiled bean sprouts, and old watery kimchi.  The only good dish was the spicy squid, but my friend found a long hair in his rice.  Service: nonexistent, as expected from a self serve place. I happened to tip $6 accidentally. When I asked for water, they told me they don't serve water and that I could buy a bottled water. I resorted to drinking tap water from their restroom because I was so thirsty.  Atmosphere: on the walls they had the typical kpop music videos but they didn't pay for premium so ads rolled between every few videos and created awkward silence.  tl;Dr - cheap owners, sub par food, and ok atmosphere.
